{
  "stem": "12768.2",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 60,
      "text": "So-- and when they were driving, they drove four hours at a time.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 61,
      "text": "And then one chauffeur slipped in and back of the other, and the other one took to the right, and then the bus kept driving.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 62,
      "text": "And my mother said when they came to Kiel, which of course, from the Kiel Canal was a German port.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 63,
      "text": "And my mother said that she could see part of a church tower.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 64,
      "text": "Otherwise, she said when she looked to the left when they driving in the bus, you could see from one side of Kiel to the other side, right through it.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 65,
      "text": "It was all flat.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 66,
      "text": "And then finally, they came up to southern Schleswig, which was at one time part of Denmark, but now is Germany.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 67,
      "text": "And she said there, it was like nothing ever had happened there, because it was just farms and all, and they were still there.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 68,
      "text": "And when they came into Denmark, they were given flowers and hugs and screams and welcome home, you know.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 69,
      "text": "My mother just said she-- she just sat there and cried.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 70,
      "text": "And then the buses went across Sweden.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 71,
      "text": "I had gone to my commander and said, I know that some-- a train is coming up to Stockholm on the 17th.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 72,
      "text": "He said, we are on ready alert.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 73,
      "text": "But he said, I'll tell you, I'll give you the trip into Stockholm.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 74,
      "text": "And you see the train, and then you come right back.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 75,
      "text": "And I said, thank you, you know, and I left.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 76,
      "text": "And I went to Stockholm.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 77,
      "text": "Unfortunately, there was two columns of trains.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 78,
      "text": "One went up to Stockholm, and the other column went to a city called Helsingborg.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 79,
      "text": "And my mother, unfortunately, was on the other train.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 80,
      "text": "But I saw an old girlfriend that had also been interned that came up.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
